Had a good look at progress on the @SouthseaCS today on a walk along the seafront. The vital scheme is the UK's largest local authority-led coastal defences project, protecting our city from flooding and preserving the area's unique heritage https://t.co/QzkOUGQtVv

@EmmaHowardBoyd @TonyJuniper @NaturalEngland @williamworsley @ForestryEngland @COP26 @EnvAgency @DefraGovUK The EA could start by properly enforcing the Farming Rules for Water and SSAFO that would at least start to protect water. Less words more do

@TonyJuniper @EmmaHowardBoyd @EnvAgency @ForestryEngland @DefraGovUK There is huge scope for @ForestryEngland to do much, much more for nature on its own estate.  Restoring the areas of #WarehamForest damaged by fire to heathland (rather than replanting with conifers/sweet chestnut) would be a great start and show positive intent.

@EmmaHowardBoyd @TonyJuniper @NaturalEngland @williamworsley @ForestryEngland @COP26 @EnvAgency @DefraGovUK OK. Will you start to deploy a TINY amount of your budget into beaver restoration? That would look like ramping up action to tackle all the things you mention.
@TomOrdePowlett @NECumbria @EnvAgency Thank you Tom! Lesson No 2 taken on board....

@EdenSwimmer @NECumbria @EnvAgency Hen fish lay about 1000 eggs per lb of body weight. Those that survive from ova - fry - parr - smolt, head to sea, return after 1 or multiple sea winters as salmon & survive in river (without eating) for long enough to spawn have defied much worse odds and completed lifecycle

urls.title: Why 2020 has been good for England's beavers
urls.description: Homes for these "ultimate environmental engineers" have been set up in enclosures across England.

tweets.text:
2020 has been a good year for beavers in England! The canals and dams beavers build alleviate flood risk and create wetlands for other species. 

400 years ago they were hunted to extinction, find out about the successes we've seen in their reintroduction: https://t.co/JSWh5o63Kd

Even when it‚Äôs rainin‚Äô, we keep on trainin‚Äô. #ADCP #Riverflow measurement training for @EnvAgencySE hydrometry teams. Vital skills to manage this summer‚Äôs ‚Äò#flought‚Äô (2012 again...?) Hope not! https://t.co/96AQ0vlLnZ

When you couldn't think the @EnvAgency record on pollution investigation and enforcement couldn't get worse, hold on ... It's going to get worse. So, carry on polluting - there's little chance of being called out, let alone fined or prosecuted. https://t.co/JvlSGUDFQT

#Worcestershire standby team Andy and Joe are out checking and monitoring  on the #Avon and #Severn this morning #Nafford #Eckington #Upton #Powick #HappyNewYear2021 @EnvAgencyMids https://t.co/FDzrYUJ0CJ
